snippet: The Labor Department reported initial benefit claims fell last week, while the Federal Reserve said household net worth rose in the fourth quarter.
abstract: Labor Dept reports initial claims for unemployment benefits fell 18,000 to seasonally adjusted 259,000 for week ended March 5; lowest claim level since October suggests continued labor market strength.
lead_paragraph: The Labor Department reported initial benefit claims fell last week, while the Federal Reserve said household net worth rose in the fourth quarter.

headline.main: Drop in Unemployment Claims Suggests Job Market Strength
headline.print_headline: Low Jobless Claims Suggest Strength in Labor Market
